<h3>Platform</h3>
<p>The platform is a web-based platform that allows all the users be able to access the data and information store in the database of the platform from anywhere using the Internet connection. </p>

<h3>Information Gathered</h3>
<p>The program is a network information database, which contains data and information from the primary credit union/cooperative on the following components;</p>
<ul>
    <li>General information of the primary credit union/cooperative</li>
    <li>Member ranges and segmentation</li>
    <li>Individual members based on Income, Age, and Gender</li>
    <li>Have less members Services (Members with less than 100USD income per month)</li>
    <li>Classification of credit union based on assets</li>
    <li>Business distribution (Usage of service)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Reporting</h3>
<p>The reporting periods for the data and information gathered in the program shall be on monthly, quarterly and annually basis. The reporting basis are Individual Report, which is the report generated from data entering in each period, monthly, quarterly and annually, and Comparison Report, which is the report generated to compare the data from different period of time, month to month, quarter to quarter, and annual to annual.</p>

<h2 style="color: #00b0f0;">RULES & REGULATION:</h2>

<h3>Data Record Timeframe</h3>

<p>The data will be recorded on a monthly basis with set due date. Each Primary Credit Union/Cooperative User, PCU, shall enter their data and information into a template provided in the platform. The Federation Administrative User, FAU, and ACCU Administrative User, AAU, can log-into the platform to see whether the data has been entered and corrected or not from the website.
</p>
<p>ACCU and federation do not have the right to edit the data entered by the primary credit union/cooperative, but can notify them to review and amend the data and/or information in case it is not tally or same with the report submitted to the federation and/or ACCU or have any irregularities. This is to create cross-reference check in the platform.</p>

<h3>Data Maintenance</h3>

<p>The General Information of each user shall be recorded to the network to identify each user. The data entered by the credit union/cooperative will be maintained for 3 years such as 2012 to 2014 as diagram below:</p>
<ul>
    <li>2012 Data: Maintain in the database as a backup</li>
    <li>2013 Data: Maintain in the database for comparison</li>
    <li>2014 Data: Maintain in the database for comparison</li>
</ul>

<p>The database uses for comparison will be 2 years only (year-to-year comparison). Once the January 2015 Data has been entered, January 2012 data shall be deleted from the program. Hence, the database will maintain data for 36 months only at all time.</p>

